# Domains excluded from external link checking (lychee).
# One regex per line, matched against the full URL.
#
# Rationale: these hosts routinely return 403/429/999 to non-browser clients
# (bot protection, aggressive rate limiting) or are otherwise flaky, which
# produces false positives that would drown out real broken links.

# Social networks with anti-bot walls (return 999 / 403 to crawlers)
https?://([a-z0-9-]+\.)?linkedin\.com
https?://([a-z0-9-]+\.)?x\.com
https?://([a-z0-9-]+\.)?twitter\.com

# The docs site's own domains — internal links are already validated at build
# time (onBrokenLinks: "throw" + scripts/check-links.py), so re-checking
# absolute self-links here only adds noise.
https?://docs\.platform\.vee\.codes
https?://docs-next\.platform\.vee\.codes

# localhost / example placeholders that appear in code samples
https?://localhost
https?://127\.0\.0\.1
https?://([a-z0-9-]+\.)?example\.(com|org|net)
